body:
@gezalore might you help me with some template type conversion magic in include/verilated_types.h pretty-please?

Below code rewritten from UVM tests/70regs/80examples/05primer gives:

```
Vt_1_t__03a__03areg_block_slave__Vclpkg__0.cpp:10:60: error: cannot convert 
      VlQueue<VlClassRef<Vt_1_t__03a__03areg_slave_TABLES>,[...]>
 to  VlQueue<VlClassRef<Vt_1_t__03a__03auvm_reg>,[...]>
 ```

TABLES properly derives from uvm_reg, and VlClassRef has the appropriate magic, but something's needed in the VlQueue (and perhaps other) containers.  Gemini made some suggestions about templated constructors being needed, but their suggestions didn't do it.

<details>
<summary>Example</summary>

```systemverilog
module t;

  class uvm_reg;
  endclass

  class reg_slave_DATA extends uvm_reg;
  endclass

  class reg_slave_TABLES extends uvm_reg;
    function uvm_reg create(string name = "");
      reg_slave_TABLES tmp;
      tmp = new;
      return tmp;
    endfunction
  endclass

  class reg_block_slave;
    reg_slave_DATA DATA;
    rand reg_slave_TABLES TABLES[256];

    virtual function void build();
      this.configure(TABLES);  // Issue was here
    endfunction

    function void configure(uvm_reg reg_a[]);
      foreach (reg_a[i])
        $display("%p", reg_a[i]);
    endfunction
  endclass

  initial begin
    reg_block_slave c;
    c = new;
    c.build;
  end

endmodule
```
</details>

